White River local, Suzette Mouton, snapped a photo of Bosbok Gas employees, Kutso Magabane and Doctor Malomane, on April 22. The two men were cleaning up the littered area and she posted the image on the Our Mbombela Facebook page. ALSO READ: City of Mbombela owes Eskom nearly R770m Mouton said in the post that Magabane and Malomane were cleaning up masses of paper spilled after a truck crashed on the R40 last week near the Manna and Plaston intersection. “Thanks to these two young men’s diligence and hard work we have a clean corner again,” said Mouton in the post.  “You two are our heroes and we thank you and your employer for caring for White River and the neatness thereof,” she said. ALSO READ: Meeting held to address crime on the Numbi Road The Our Mbombela movement was launched earlier this year to create a safer, cleaner and friendly Mbombela with the help of local communities, organisations and businesses.